27:41.432 --> 27:45.497
Russian officer in that attack. And anyway, he got 
sent home. And I don't remember his rank. He was a

27:52.225 --> 27:55.009
lieutenant colonel or maybe a colonel. And when he 
got home, they told him he needed to go to

27:56.110 --> 27:59.434
Washington. He was really worried, and he got 
there. His family was there. They presented him

28:02.583 --> 28:05.245
with the Medal of Honor. And he said he had no idea. 
He thought he was in trouble. I have a friend that

28:08.869 --> 28:15.315
was in the Army that received the Medal of Honor. 
And he was a Holocaust pilot. And he didn't feel

28:17.517 --> 28:20.240
that he deserved it either. He said that he was just 
doing his duty the way he felt it. He told me, he

28:26.706 --> 28:28.408
said... Westmoreland, the politicians, 
Johnson, needed heroes really bad because of the

28:28.878 --> 28:38.369
attitude of the American people. And he said he 
felt like that was the reason he got the Medal of

28:38.389 --> 28:42.153
Honor. Now, I think the guy did a tremendous job. 
They killed 400 or 500 enemy troops. Fred

28:48.019 --> 28:57.450
Ferguson, this friend of mine, he took a 
helicopter gunships in and he... protected them

28:58.679 --> 29:03.985
while they landed and brought up a whole bunch of, 
freed a whole bunch of prisoners. And there's a

29:06.028 --> 29:14.558
book that's been written that he's listed in 
there, and he's told me before that he says, I

29:06.028 --> 29:14.558
didn't do nothing. But I really, I think most of 
them do, and they are humble. I think it's just a

29:19.824 --> 29:22.086
question of being humble. There was guys that got 
medals, you know, for Purple hearts were handed

29:24.616 --> 29:26.659
out pretty freely. I knew guys that run through 
